JOHN TALIAFERRO, 1000 acs. (N.
L.), Spotsyl. Co., in St. George’s Par;
on the SW Mountains, above the Mountain Run; 2 Nov. 1726, p. 10.

SAME. 750 acs. (N, L.); same Co.
& date; page 15. Adj, Major Harrison;
& Mayo's land. 3 Lbs., 15 Shill.

WILLIAM GENT, of Pr. Geo. Co;
376 acs. (N. L.), Brunswick Co; on
both sides of Sturgion Run, on S. side
of Nottoway River; at his 1st survey;
on the Beaver Pond Branch; 31 Oct.
1726, p. 58.

JAMES PITTILLO, of Pr. Geo. Co;
242 acs, (N. L.), Brunswick-Gu; om S.
side of Waqua Creek; 31 Oc, 1726, p.
8, ;

