Hanover Co; on N. side of the Little
River; adj. Samuel Reynolds; James
Glen; James Brown; & Kimbrow’s line;
16 June 1727, p. 102. 15 Shill.

THOMAS HAMM, 400 acs. (N. L.),
King Wm. Co., in St. Margaret's Par;
on §. side the Reedy Swamp; adj. Edward Arnold: & Robert Axton’s line;
16 Juae 1727, p. 110. 40 Shill.

ROBERT MUNFORD, GENT., of
Pr, Geo. Co; 290 acs. (N. L.), Brunswick Co; on S. side of Maherin River;
between plantations of Major Munford
& John Linch; on David Crawley’s line;
16 June 1727, p. 112.

WILLIAM WEAVER, of Pr. Geo.
€o; 180 acs, (N. L.), Brunswick Co;
on both sides of Fountain’s Creek; just
below mouth of the Beverdam Creek;
16 June 1727, p, 118.

GEORGE BOOTH, of Surry Co;
1054 acs. (N. L.), Pr. Geo. Co; on
both sides of Turkey Egg Cr; adj. his
own survey; & William Tucker’s line;
16 June 1727, p. 124. 5 Lbs., 5 Shill.

JAMES WILSON, Planter; 120 acs.
(N. 1.) Pr. Anne Co., in Black Water;
16 June 1727, p. 146. 15 Shill.

WILLIAM RANDOLPH, GENT.,
6350 acs. (O. & N. L.), Henrico Co;
on N. side of Appamattock Riv; adj.
Capt. Richard Randolph; John Stewart;
& Col. William Randolph; crossing
Beavorpond Br. of Fiting Cr; to N.
side of sd. river at a poynt of Rocks;
17 Aug, 1727, p. 157. 4400 acs. part
granted him, 16 Mar. 1724. 9 Lbs.,
15 Shill.

ROGER TANDY, of K. & Q. Co;
520 acs. (N. L.), Spotsyl. Co., in St.
George’s Par; adj. Mr. Robert Baylor;
Mr. Harry Beverley’s new line; & Capt.
John Camm & Mr. Saml. Smith; 13
Oct, 1727, p. 169.

FRANCIS YOUNG, of South Carrolina; 300 acs. (N. L.), Brunswick Co;
on E. side of Roanoak River; in the
County Line; 13 Oct. 1727, p. 174.

JOHN SIMMONS, JUNR., of Surry
Co; 312 acs, (N. L.), Brunswick Co;
on N, side of the great Creek; near br.
Rose's Creek; on land of John Rose;
13 Oct. 1727, p. 178.

GEORGE HAGOOD, of Surty Co;
345 acs, (N. L.), Brunswick Co; N.
side of Maherin River; on the Sappony
Indian Line, on E. side of Totera Creek;
adj. Charles Lucas; 13 Oct. 1727, p.
179.

NICHOLAS JARRARD, 150 acs. (N.
L.), Surry Co; S. side the main Blackwater Sw; on W. side of Parker's Br;
13 Oct. 1727, p, 250. 15 Shill,

JOHN EIDY, of W’moreland Co;
536 acs. (N. L.), Spotsyl. Co., in St.
George’s Par; on S. side the North
River, in the gr. fork of Rappa. River;
adj, William Beverley; & Henry Willis’
line; 12 June 1728, p. 262.

JURY SMITH. 450 acs. (N. L.),
King Wm. Co., in St, Margaret’s Par;
bet. brs. of the South River & Polecat
(Sw.) ; adj. James Powell & Ja. Taylor;
John Wright; Timothy Chandlor;
Thomas Hamm; Joseph Chandlor; &
Mr. Wm. Terrell; 13 Oct. 1727, p. 283.
45 Shill.

CORTNEY NORMAN, 238 acs. (N.
L.), Spotsyl. Co., in St. George’s Par;
in the gr. forke of Rappa, Riv; on S.
side of the S. fork of the North Riv;
into the Goardvine fork; 28 Sept. 1728,
p. 302.

PAULIN BRROKE, of K. & Q. Co;
1000 acs. (N. L.), Spotsyl. Co; at foot
of the gr. Mts; adj, Humphry Brook;
George Brooke; George Pen; & Zachasias Taylor; 28 Sept. 1728, p. 341.
(GEORGE BROOKE, of K. & Q. Co;
1000 acs. (N. L.), Sporsyl. Co; near
the gr. Mts; adj. George Penn; &
Paulin Brooke; on the Ocinng line; 28
Sept, 1728, p, 342.

RICHARD MALDEN, 100 acs. (N.
L.), Spotsyl, Co., in St. George’s Par;
in the Ist fork of Rappidan Riv; by the
Island Run; cor. of Thomas Weyland;
28 Sept. 1728, p. 343.

HENRY MADISON, of K, & Q. Co;
1000 acs, (N. L.), Spotsyl. Co; adj.
James Madison; George Penn; & Zacharias Taylor's line; 28 Sept. 1728, p, 352.

EPHRAIM PARRUM, of Surry Co;
338 acs. (N. L.), Brunswick Co; on N.
side of Reedy Cr; adj. Charles Kimball ;
& land of John Jackson; 28 Sept. 1728,
p. 358.

JOHN LONDON, of K. & Q. Co;
950 acs. (N. L.), Spotsyl. Co., in St.
George’s Par; on brs. of Terry’s Run;
adj. Mr. Harty Beverley; on S. side of
Avsforemust; Mrs. Hannah Clowder;
& Musick & Allen, on S. side of Capt.
Clowder's path; 28 Sept. 1728, p. 371.

CAPT. THOMAS DANCIE (Danzie), Mariner, of the City of London;
4553 acs. (N. L.), Hanover Co; on
both sides of Camp & Bunches Creeks;
adj. Capt, Charles Hudson, Capt. Christopher Clark, & Mr, George Webb; 28
June 1729, p. 376, 22 Lbs., 15 Shill.

JAMES JONES, 74 acs. (N. L.),
Essex Co., in St. Mary’s- Par; on N.
side of the S. fork of Pumondsend Sw;
adj. Enock Dowdy; Warwick Camock;
Walter Jones; & Col. Robert Beverley;
28 Sept. 1728, p. 377. 10 Shill.

JOHN HUFFMAN, 800 acs. (N.
L.), Spotsyl. Co., in St. George’s Par;
in the gr. forke of Rappa. (Riv.), on
the Deep Run; adj. Michael Wilhide;
27 Sept. 1729, p. 388.

ANDREW KIRKER, 850 acs. (N,
L.}, Spotsyl. Co., in St. George’s Par;
in the Ist forke of the Rapperdan Riv;
on N. side of the White Oak Run
below the Island; 28 Sept. 1728, p. 389.

CHRISTOPHER SIMMERMAN, 280
acs. (N. L.), Spotsyl. Co. in Sr.
George's Par; in the fork of Rappa.
River, on brs, of Brookes’ Run; adj.
John Quarles;
Pollard’s line;

WILLIAM HEATH, of Pr, Geo. Co;
100 acs. (N. L.), Isle of Wight Co;
on N. side of the Three Creeks; on
SW side of the great Swamp; adj.
Thomas Griffs’. (Griffis’) land; 28 Sept.
1728, p. 394. 10 Shill.

JOHN GATEWOOD, 450 acs. (N.
L.), Essex Co., in South Farnham Par;
on N. side of Hoskins’ percorson; adj,
Gouldman & Meriwether; land of
Howel, formerly Alexander Robbins’;
Coleman's line; James Renolds; crossing
Holly Br; to Upshaw’s & Waller's land;
27 Sept. 1729, p. 395. 45 Shill.

JOHN BROWN, 240 acs. (N. L.),
Surry Co; on S, side of Nottoway Riv;
corner of Maj, Benjamin Harrison &
William Smith; on John Davis’ line;
27 Sept. 1729, p. 395. 25 Shill.

SAME. 400 acs. (N, L.); same location, date, & page. Adj. Col. Cole;
crossing fork of the Indian Camp Br.
40 Shill.

ISAAC ALLEN, 50 acs. (N. L.),
Caroline Co., in St. Margaret's Par; on
brs. of the Reedy Sw; corner of Mr.
William Oglevie & Nicholas Dillard;
on lines of Henry Isbell; & Paul Pigg;
27 Sept. 1727, p. 400. 5 Shill.

HENRY ANDERSON, GENT., of
Henrico Co; 1800 acs. (N. L.), Pr.
Geo. Co; on upper side of Knib’s Cr;
at Cobbs’ corner on the Beach Tree Br;
& on a large br. of Flatt Cr; 27 Sept.
1729, p. 403. 9 Lbs., Money.

JOHN PARTLO, 200 acs. (N. L.),
Caroline Co., in St. Margaret's Par;
beg. about 200 yds. above his house;
adj, John Nichols; John Martin; & John
Ellis; on W. side of White's Run; 27
Sept. 1729, p. 415. 40 Shill,

JOSEPH HAWKINS, 670 acs. (N.
L.), Spotsyl. Co., in St. George’s Par;
N. side the N. fork of the Northanna
(Riv.) ; on NE side of Hawkins’ Tract;
& on E. side of a Beverdam Run; 28
Sept, 1728, p. 425.

THOMAS BOTTOM, of Henrico Co;
400 acs. (N. L.), Pr. Geo, Co; on the
main fork of West's Cr. of Deep Creek;
on N. fork of Buckskin Creek; 6 June
1730, p. 450. 40 Shill.

THOMAS HUCKABY, 316 acs, (N.
L.), Brunswick Co; adj. at his own;
& Wilson’s line; 28 Sept. 1728, p. 457.

THOMAS RUCKER, 876 acs. (N.
L.), Spotsyl. Co., in St. George’s Par;
adj. Thomas Jackson; & John Rucker;
16 June 1730, p. 458.

FRANCIS MICHAEL, 400 acs. (N.
L.), Spotsy!l. Co., in St. George's Par;
in the gr. fork of Rappa. River; at head
of Michael's Br; adj. Augustine Smith;
John Finlason: & Mauttoon Lewis; 28
Sept. 1728, p. 473.

THOMAS WRIGHT, 251 acs, (N.
L.), Spotsyl. Co., in St. George's Par;
in the gr. fork of Rappa. Riv; adj.
Connorat’ Ambyon; Christopher- Simmerman; Richard ‘Right; John Finlason;
& John Asher; 28 Sept. 1728, p. 475.

RICHARD WRIGHT, 250 acs. (N.
L.), Spotsyl. Co., in St. George’s Par;
in the gr. fork of Rappa, Riv; adj.
Christopher Simmerman; John Finlason;
& John Quarles; 28 Sept. 1728, p. 475.

HENRY WOOD, GENT., of Goochland Co; 200 acs. (N, L.), Hanover
Co; between lines of Watson & Alves;
28 Sept. 1730, p. 502. 20 Shill.

HON. WILLIAM BYRD, ESQR.,
1550 acs. (N. L.), Brunswick Co; including 2 Islands, on N. side of Roanoak River; adj. Capt. James Munford;
28 Sept. 1730, p. 504. 7 Lbs., 15 Shill.

PETER DEP, 400 acs. (N. L.),
Goochland Co; S. side of James River;
on W. side of the low, Manakin Creek;
28 Sept. 1730, p. 507. 40 Shill,
